  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "6iIU6SpKJiOhKDKHfFi9Fshjmsc=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:26.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "The `DocumentToolbar` component provides a layered styling architecture with clear separation of concerns:\n\n## Layer 1: Container\nThe toolbar's outer container (background, border, rounding) is controlled via the `className` prop, which uses `twMerge` to merge custom classes with defaults. Default classes: `flex h-12 w-full items-center justify-between rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-slate-50 px-4`.\n\n## Layer 2: Buttons\nInternal buttons (undo, redo, export, history, close) use hardcoded Tailwind classes and don't expose their own style props. Customization requires Tailwind arbitrary child selectors passed through the parent `className` prop.\n\n## Layer 3: Revision History Panel\nThe revision history panel is rendered by Connect outside the editor component tree. It lives inside `#document-editor-context` in the DOM and can only be styled via scoped CSS in `style.css`.\n\nThis three-layer architecture means theming a toolbar requires understanding which technique applies at each level \u2014 direct className for the container, child selectors for buttons, and external CSS for the history panel.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:26.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:26.000Z"
    }
  },
